id: pm-ybiz
title: pm-changelog classifier mis-routes feature titles containing the word 'remove'/'delete' into the Removed section
description: "The pm-changelog classifyItem 'Removed' rule fires on \\bremove\\b/\\bdelete\\b anywhere in allValues (strong tier + sanitized title) BEFORE the strong-tier Changed/type defaults. A closed item whose title legitimately contains 'remove-type' as part of a feature name (e.g. the schema-customization plan 'Complete schema customization epic: remove-type, add-status, ...') is published under '### Removed', which misleads readers into thinking a capability was removed. The existing flag-stripping guard only neutralizes --flags, not plain words like 'remove-type'."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 4
tags[5]: "area:changelog","area:ci",classifier,living-map,pm-changelog
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:38:58.087Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T13:01:28.749Z"
assignee: codex-active-pm-cycle-20260607
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- A title containing 'remove'/'delete' only as a substring of a feature/command name is NOT routed to Removed when type+tags carry no removal signal\\n- Strong-tier (type/tags) signals can override the weak title-only Removed match (mirroring the Changed/Added precedence)\\n- Regression test covers 'remove-type'/'create_default_type'-style titles\\n- Verified against the live pm-cli tracker (e.g. pm-z5nb no longer mis-routes)"
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: low
confidence: high
